ò (questa iscrizione) a suo fratello\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>  \u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Mommsen 1883 \u003Ca href=\"http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/item/buchseite/650772\" target=\"_blank\">7193\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000589\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000589\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\">\u003Cp>The letters show the beginnings of a shift towards the later cursive style, with extended serifs on the A and M, T tending to be narrow with upward sloping head, E likewise tall, narrow, with top stroke sloping upwards. Interpuncts, sometimes in the form of hedera, used between all words except after Calbentius\u003C/p> Line 1  10-11  Line 2  11-13  Line 3  10-13  Line 4  11-13  Line 5  11-14  Interlineation line 1 to 2  11  Interlineation line 2 to 3  5-8  Interlineation line 3 to 4  5-8  Interlineation line 4 to 5  4-5  \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[247,250,253,256,259,261,264,267,270],{"id":248,"html":249},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"la\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>D(is) · M(anibus) · \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Calbentius Motho\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Calbentius\">Calbentius\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Motho\">Motho\u00